There were 1.22 million Japanese who
last year reached 20, the age of legal maturity, the Japan
Statistics Bureau reported yesterday. The increase was the
smallest since the bureau began tracking the number in 1968, and
compares with a peak of 2.46 million new adults in 1970.  To contact the reporters on this story:
